getResultLine

public java.lang.String getResultLine()
Description copied from interface: AlgorithmRun
Note: This should always return a well-formatted result line. It may NOT necessarily correspond to values that the methods return. (i.e. You should be able to use this output as standard output without any validation, but it may not correspond to what we got this time) Some extreme examples are when we clean up messy wrappers output (for instance SAT >= timeout). Depending on how the cleanup is done, this may change the result flagged, or we may massage the timeout.
